column13: Clear. Some bank veg submerged on either side
column14: Good wade measurement 5m d/s of gauge. Using Pre and post DWL fro MGH since swapped logger during mmnt. A few angle errors on LB and close to RB. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Large SRC found and trace painting. Suspect orifice silted. Long heavy purge and HG stabilized at 0.615 based on polled values. Orifice tip clear. HG2 invalid. Upper intake exposed and lower connection is poor. Pulled power for logger swap at 10:03. Reset HG for 10:25 value, but SDI cord was still loose. Reset took but missed 10:25 logged value due to loose sdi connection. HG valid from 10:30 onwards Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: Clear.
column14: Good wade mmnt 10m d/s. Couple angle errors and SNR errors from bank veg MGH calc in field review tab @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ HG tracking well. One spike to 0.653 at 11:35 but the rest of the logged values look good. HG2 had a large reset but this was expected since it had been pinned and unpinned during the off season and hadn't recieved a valid WL set until now. Flushed well at 11:51 and then well recovered to 0.784, so well must not have been connected. Upper intake exposed and was quite muddy when flushed. I can not see where the lower intake is coming out but flushed quite a few buckets so hopefully its open. WL hasn't changed according to accubar so I reset HG2 (SE) for the 12:10 reading. HG2 is suspect data.  Mid-section
